Package: unwindprotect
Type: Package
Title: Example of using R's unwind protection with C++ objects
Version: 0.1.0
Author: David Cortes
Maintainer: David Cortes <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: Example about using R's unwind protection system to trigger
    stack unwinding (destruction) of C++ objects when an R error is triggered
    from compiled code inside '.Call'.
License: BSD_2_clause
Encoding: UTF-8
NeedsCompilation: yes
